## Comprehensive Keyboard Accessibility Test Report

### Test Environment
- **Application**: @emoji-mart/monorepo (Storybook)
- **URL**: http://localhost:6006
- **Date**: April 15, 2026
- **Test Context**: storybook-preview-iframe (iframe content)

### Test 1: Search Input Focus
✅ **PASS** - The search input (`input#emoji-mart-search-1`) can be focused by clicking on it. The search functionality works (typing "smile" filters the emoji results to "Search Results").

### Test 2: Arrow Key Navigation (No Filter)
❌ **FAIL** - Pressing Down, Right, Left, Up arrow keys from the focused search input does NOT navigate to any emoji in the emoji grid. No visual focus indicator appears on any emoji after pressing arrow keys.

### Test 3: Arrow Key Navigation (With "smile" Filter)
❌ **FAIL** - After typing "smile" and filtering the emoji list to show "Search Results", pressing Down, Right, Left arrow keys still does NOT navigate to any emoji in the filtered results. No visual focus indicator appears.

### Test 4: Arrow Key Navigation After Clicking Emoji
❌ **FAIL** - After clicking on an emoji (which selects it and shows its preview), pressing Right arrow does NOT navigate to the next emoji. Keyboard navigation between emoji items via arrow keys is completely non-functional.

### Test 5: ARIA Role on Search Input
❌ **FAIL** - The search input (`<input type="search" id="emoji-mart-search-1">`) has:
  - **No explicit `role` attribute** (implicit role is `searchbox` from `type="search"`)
  - **Missing `role="combobox"`** which is required for a search input that controls a listbox of suggestions
  - **Missing `aria-autocomplete`** attribute
  - **Missing `aria-controls`** attribute pointing to the emoji list
  - **Missing `aria-haspopup`** attribute
  - **Missing `aria-expanded`** attribute
  - ✅ Has accessible name "Search" from associated `<label class="emoji-mart-sr-only">` element

### Test 6: ARIA Role on Emoji List Container
❌ **FAIL** - The emoji scroll container (`div.emoji-mart-scroll`) has:
  - **No ARIA attributes** at all
  - **`Role: generic`** (implicit, no semantic meaning)
  - **No accessible name** (`Name: ""`)
  - DevTools Accessibility: "Element not interesting for accessibility"
  - Missing `role="listbox"` or `role="grid"`
  - Missing `aria-label` for the emoji list

### Test 7: ARIA Attributes on Emoji Items
❌ **FAIL** - Individual emoji items (`span.emoji-mart-emoji.emoji-mart-emoji-native`) have:
  - **No ARIA attributes** at all
  - **`Role: generic`** (implicit, SPAN element - not interactive!)
  - **No accessible name** (`Name: ""`)
  - **`tabIndex: -1`** (not in keyboard tab order)
  - DevTools Accessibility: "Element not interesting for accessibility"
  - Missing `role="option"` or `role="gridcell"`
  - Missing `aria-label` with emoji name

### Test 8: Emoji List Accessible Title
❌ **FAIL** - The emoji list and its "Search Results" category label (`div.emoji-mart-category-label`) both have:
  - **No accessible heading/label structure**
  - The text "Search Results" is visible but has `Role: generic` and `Name: ""`
  - The category container has `data-name="Search"` but this is not an ARIA attribute

### Test 9: Category Navigation Buttons
⚠️ **PARTIAL** - The category filter buttons (`<button>` elements) at the top have:
  - ✅ `aria-label` attributes (e.g., "Frequently Used", "Smileys & Emotion")
  - ❌ No explicit `role` attribute (but implicit `button` role from element type is acceptable)
  - ✅ Keyboard accessible via Tab key (they are `<button>` elements)

### Summary

| Accessibility Feature | Status | Details |
|----------------------|--------|---------|
| Search input focus | ✅ PASS | Click to focus works |
| Arrow key navigation (no filter) | ❌ FAIL | No keyboard navigation |
| Arrow key navigation (with filter) | ❌ FAIL | No keyboard navigation |
| Search input role (combobox) | ❌ FAIL | role is `searchbox`, not `combobox` |
| Search input ARIA attrs | ❌ FAIL | Missing all combobox ARIA attributes |
| Emoji list ARIA role | ❌ FAIL | `Role: generic`, should be `listbox`/`grid` |
| Emoji list accessible name | ❌ FAIL | No aria-label on emoji list |
| Emoji items ARIA role | ❌ FAIL | SPAN elements, `Role: generic` |
| Emoji items accessible name | ❌ FAIL | No aria-label on emoji items |
| Emoji items keyboard focusable | ❌ FAIL | `tabIndex: -1`, not reachable |
| Category buttons | ⚠️ PARTIAL | Have aria-label but no tab navigation support from search |

The emoji picker has **significant keyboard accessibility deficiencies**. The core issues are:
1. **No keyboard navigation** between emoji items using arrow keys
2. **No combobox ARIA semantics** on the search input
3. **No accessible labels** on the emoji list and emoji items
4. **Emoji items are generic SPAN elements**, not interactive elements

Based on these findings, the emoji picker fails the WCAG 2.1 success criteria for keyboard accessibility (SC 2.1.1 Keyboard, SC 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value).
